# ARES — codebase conventions

You have the ARES MCP tools, which hold this team's learned written and unwritten
rules. Treat them as **binding context**.

## FIRST, once per repo per session

0. Before your first `recall_decisions` in a repo, call `ares.ensure_repo_memory`
   with `repo` ("owner/repo", lowercase). It learns the repo from its docs and PR
   reviews if new, and is an instant no-op if already learned. Do this once.

## BEFORE writing or modifying any non-trivial code

1. Call `ares.recall_decisions({ query, repo })` describing what you're about to
   implement. Follow any applicable rule; if you must deviate, cite `[id]`.

## AFTER writing code (before finishing your turn)

2. Call `ares.check_conflict({ repo, intent, snippet })`. If it returns conflicts,
   rewrite to comply or explain the intentional override and cite `[id]`.

## When a durable rule is established

Call `ares.record_decision({ repo, statement, rationale })`.

Do not skip `recall_decisions` — the mistake should never get typed.
